---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <nav
        class="w-full px-8 py-6 flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10"
    >
        <a
            href="/#work"
            class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"
            >← Back to Home</a
        >
        <h1
            class="text-sm font-serif-elegant tracking-wide text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
        >
            Saurabh Sawant
        </h1>
    </nav>
    <main class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center w-full pb-32">
        <header class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 pt-24 pb-16">
            <p
                class="text-xs tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-4"
            >
                Franka Panda · Apr 2023 - Jul 2023
            </p>
            <h1
                class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif-elegant text-slate-900 dark:text-white leading-tight mb-8"
            >
                Image-Guided Robotic Needle Placement
            </h1>
            <div
                class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10 pt-8"
            >
                <span>ROS</span><span>•</span><span>Python</span><span>•</span><span>Kinematics</span><span>•</span><span>Path Planning</span><span>•</span><span>Trajectory Planning</span>
            </div>
        </header>
        <div class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 mb-16">
            <div
                class="w-full aspect-video bg-slate-100 dark:bg-[#111] relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl shadow-sm dark:shadow-none"
            >
                <img
                    src="/Franka.png"
                    alt="Franka Emika Panda Robot"
                    class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-90"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <article
            class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed space-y-12 text-lg text-justify mt-8"
        >
            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Overview & Course Context
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Developed as part of the "Robotics and Navigation in
                    Medicine" course at TUHH (MTEC), this project aimed to
                    simulate and execute a modern image-guided robotic surgery.
                    The primary objective was to accurately identify a tumor's
                    position and autonomously maneuver a 7-axis Franka Emika
                    robotic arm to perform a minimally invasive needle biopsy.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Project Structure
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    The development was split between two specialized sub-teams:
                    Vision and Robotics. I focused entirely on the Robotics
                    aspect.
                </p>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Vision Team:</strong
                        > Handled depth camera calibration and image processing to
                        output two critical 3D spatial coordinates: the target tumor
                        location and the optimal entry point on the patient to minimize
                        tissue damage.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Robotics Team (My Role):</strong
                        > Responsible for translating those 3D coordinates into smooth,
                        safe, and precise physical movements of the robotic manipulator.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Trajectory Planning & Control
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Safe medical robotics requires mathematically continuous and
                    jerk-free motion. To achieve this, our team implemented the
                    underlying motion control architecture using ROS and Python.
                </p>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Trajectory Algorithms:</strong
                        > We wrote two different trajectory planning algorithms—Quintic Polynomials and LSPB (Linear Segment with Parabolic Blends). We evaluated both approaches and chose the better-performing one to guarantee continuous position, velocity, and acceleration profiles, eliminating abrupt hardware jerks during operation.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Straight-Line Interpolation:</strong
                        > Engineered custom interpolation algorithms to constrain
                        the needle's path to a strict straight line from the entry
                        point to the tumor, which is critical for minimizing surgical
                        invasiveness.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >ROS Node Integration:</strong
                        > Encapsulated the planning logic within a dedicated ROS node
                        to handle the dynamic pose targeting and execution seamlessly.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Challenges & Implementation
                </h3>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Manual Inverse Kinematics:</strong
                        > Instead of relying on high-level abstractions like MoveIt,
                        the inverse kinematics for the 7-axis arm were calculated
                        and implemented manually. This provided a much deeper understanding
                        of redundant manipulator motion and singularity avoidance.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Sim-to-Real Gap:</strong
                        > Bridging the gap between RViz simulations and the physical
                        Franka robot required rigorous debugging. Motions that appeared
                        flawless in simulation occasionally triggered safety limits
                        on the real hardware, demanding iterative refinements to the
                        trajectory parameters.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
